text: Another question which is not meant to be disrespectful. @cnbc talks about "the uninterrupted final minutes of the trading session" like its the Master Tournament or a tied World Series game (and then launches into a commercial). Maybe its just "me."

All I can say Rev is that when I was a 21 year old housing analyst at Kidder Peabody I didnt know the "convention" and was even more of a skeptic and wise guy than I am now! I can tell you stories of tough questions I used to ask during road shows. Nearly got me fired many times
Rev I am always reminded of Mickey Mantle who said: "I never knew the game of baseball was so easy until I entered the broadcasting booth."

These talking heads' market commentaryare a wonder to behold. Mostly non rigorous, seat of the pants and made up. And when recommendations arent memorialized its easy to talk the talk. And said with such confidence. Beware, "the Cossacks may be coming."
